The problem below is caused because in the latest build Platform.getBundle("org.eclipse.swt.carbon.macosx.ppc") now returns null.  It looks like it's been changed to "org.eclipse.swt.carbon.macosx".  Previously we calculated the name of the eclipse plug-in for all platforms using this code:
"org.eclipse.swt."+Platform.getWS()+"."+Platform.getOS()+"."+Platform.getOSArch();
I guess this is no longer valid with both ppc and x86 being bundled in the same plug-in.
